Sanford senior Dylan Gendron drives around Andre Hicks III of Westbrook during a game at Sanford on Jan. 6. (Gregory Rec/Staff Photographer)

Sanford isn’t known as a Maine high school powerhouse program, but things have [come together for the Spartans](https://www.pressherald.com/2026/01/07/sanford-boys-basketball-off-to-rare-red-hot-start/) this season. They are off to an 10-0 start and sit atop the Class A South Heal point standings. They’ve also taken over the top spot in the Varsity Maine boys basketball poll.

[![](https://www.pressherald.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/4/2026/01/41290036_20250218_YorkSpruceMountain_Boys_2_0320_a0861b.jpg?w=250&h=250&crop=1)](https://www.pressherald.com/2026/01/13/five-maine-boys-basketball-storylines-this-week/)

