[Five Maine boys basketball storylines this week](https://www.pressherald.com/2026/01/13/five-maine-boys-basketball-storylines-this-week/)

Sanford added wins over Westbrook, Thornton Academy and Bonny Eagle since the previous poll to overtake [last week’s](https://www.sunjournal.com/2026/01/06/varsity-maine-boys-basketball-poll-2/) No. 1, Camden Hills, which also is unbeaten at 9-0.

Other than the switch at the top, this week’s top five is the same. Gardiner has moved up two spots to sixth, and Brunswick joins the rankings at No. 7.

